    "text": "Nothing to read into a single morning like this. Resting heart rate is simply how fast your heart beats at complete rest, and it commonly drifts up a beat or two after alcohol, a salty meal, or a later night — you logged all three. Your resting heart rate of 61 bpm is a touch over your 30-day baseline of 57.8 bpm, which is the kind of small bump that usually settles within a night or two once you're back to routine. With no symptoms and your other trends steady, carry on as normal. If it stayed elevated for several days running or came with symptoms like chest discomfort or unusual fatigue, that would be worth a doctor visit — this isn't that.",
